# Solving the `soundness` Theorem in Lean 4

We need to prove the `soundness` theorem, which states that for any `c : Circuit p (ZMod p)`, the evaluation of `c` is equal to the evaluation of its corresponding `Cs` representation. The proof proceeds by induction on `c`.

The theorem is:
```tactics
theorem soundness : ÔłÇ (c : Circuit p (ZMod p)),
  rw_bisim (Circuit.eval c) (Cs.eval (to_cs c)) := by
```

The induction is set up as:
```tactics
intro c
induction c with
| nil =>
  simp [Circuit.eval, to_cs]
  constructor
| lam k h =>
  simp [Circuit.eval, to_cs]
  constructor
  exact h
```

For the `eq0` case:
```tactics
| eq0 e c h =>
  simp [Circuit.eval, Cs.eval, to_cs]
  split
  apply h
```

For the `share` case:
```tactics
| share e c h =>
  simp [Circuit.eval, Cs.eval, to_cs]
  apply rw_bisim.right
  intro x
  simp [Exp.eval]
  split
  have hmy : x = Exp.eval e := by grind
  rw [<-hmy]
  apply h
```

For the `is_zero` case:
```tactics
| is_zero e c h =>
  apply rw_bisim.right
  intro inv
  apply rw_bisim.right
  intro o
  simp [Exp.eval, Circuit.eval, Cs.eval]
  split
  case is_zero.h.h.isTrue he0 =>
    split
